== Forms ==

[[File:Ikegami-sone ruins04s3200.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Reconstruction of a raised-floor building in the "roof-storehouse" style at the [[Ikegami-Sone Site]] in {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Prefecture|qq=}}.]]

Raised-floor buildings are thought to have existed in two forms: one with walls above the floor, and another called "roof-storehouses" (屋根倉, *Yanegura*), where the roof (usually {{ill|gabled|ja|切妻屋根|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/gabled|qq=}}) rests directly on the floor without walls.{{Sfn|Agency for Cultural Affairs, Monuments Division|2013|p=165}} The typical {{ill|raised-floor warehouse|ja|高床倉庫|1=Raised-floor warehouse|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/raised-floor warehouse|13=User:Immanuelle/Raised-floor warehouse|qq=}}
 is reconstructed with walls, based on findings from sites like the {{ill|Toro site|ja|登呂遺跡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toro site|qq=}} and {{ill|Yamaki site|ja|山木遺跡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamaki site|qq=}} in {{ill|Shizuoka Prefecture|ja|静岡県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shizuoka Prefecture|qq=}}. Roof-storehouse style reconstructions can be seen in large posthole buildings at the {{ill|Ikegami-Sone Site|ja|池上・曽根遺跡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikegami-Sone Site|qq=}} spanning {{ill|Izumi|ja|和泉市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izumi|qq=}} and {{ill|Izumiotsu|ja|泉大津市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izumiotsu|qq=}} in {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Prefecture|qq=}}.{{Sfn|Agency for Cultural Affairs, Monuments Division|2013|p=165}}

